@group
    @title=hrd files
    @key=hrd
    @ingroup=config-files
    @brief=The article describes HRD configuration files.

    The hrd files for the console are located in the [c]colorer/hrd/console[/c] folder. Each file corresponds to one
    color scheme. The file name is the name of the scheme.

    An hrd file is an XML file containing the set of [c]assign[/c] key, each key assigns a color to a syntax or XCE region.

    The list of the syntax region names can be found in the [c]colorer/hrc/common.jar/lib/default.hrc[/c] file.

    The list of XCE regions are shown in the table below:
    @table
        @row
            @col
                xce:TextColor
            @end
            @col
                The default color for the text.
            @end
        @end
        @row
            @col
                xce:CurrentLineTextColor
            @end
            @col
                The color for the current line of the text.
            @end
        @end
        @row
            @col
                xce:BlockTextColor
            @end
            @col
                The default color for the text inside the block.
            @end
        @end
        @row
            @col
                xce:CurrentLineBlockTextColor
            @end
            @col
                The color for the current line of the text inside the block.
            @end
        @end
        @row
            @col
                xce:StatusLineColor
            @end
            @col
                The color of the XCE status line.
            @end
        @end
        @row
            @col
                xce:SpellCheckErrorColor
            @end
            @col
                The color to be used to highlight spell checking errors.
            @end
        @end
        @row
            @col
                xce:PairHighlightColor
            @end
            @col
                The color to be used to highlight the matching syntax pairs (e.g. brackets).
            @end
        @end

        @row
